<div class="bracken" style="background-color: #fffef2">
<div class="main_housing" style="max-width: 728px; display: block; margin: 0 auto;">
<div class="text-block-underneath">
<h2 style="margin-bottom: 2em"><a href="https://thewalrus.ca/category/poetry/">POETRY</a> / <a href="https://thewalrus.ca/category/issues/july-august-2023/">JULY/AUGUST 2023</a></h2>
<h4 role="img" aria-label="Map" style="margin:0!important";><img src="https://walrus-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/img/SR23_Klassen_Map_1.jpg" alt="Map" width="115" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-156690" /></h4>
<h2 style="margin: 2em 0 0 0 !important;">BY <a href="https://thewalrus.ca/author/daniel-scott-tysdal/">PHILLIP CRYMBLE</a></h2>
<p>    <span style="font-size: 0.8rem; font-family:'Source Sans Pro'; font-weight: 100;">Published 6:30, Aug. 2, 2023</span><br />
<div class="su-spacer" style="height:20px"></div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="main_housing" style="max-width: 728px; display: block; margin: 0 auto;">
<p><iframe style='width: 100%; height: 100px; border: none; position: relative; z-index: 1;' allowtransparency allow="clipboard-read; clipboard-write" src="https://narrations.ad-auris.com/widget/the-walrus-/map"></iframe></p>
<div class="poem-indent">
<span class="line-indent" style="margin-left: 4em;"> The trays of coloured pencils on the table.</span><br />
Your list of lakes and waterways. Careful</p>
<p><span class="line-indent" style="margin-left: 7.75em;">not to come too close to coastlines&mdash;I crudely</span><br />
<span class="line-indent" style="margin-left: 4em;">shade the bigger bays and basins&mdash;surround</span></p>
<p>the land you’ve laboured at in Copenhagen blue.<br />
<span class="line-indent" style="margin-left: 7.75em;">Another year of middle school&mdash;and now&mdash;</span></p>
<p><span class="line-indent" style="margin-left: 4em;">like last October&mdash;I try to help out how I can&mdash;</span><br />
attempt to be of use. On Sundays&mdash;back in ’82&mdash;  </p>
<p><span class="line-indent" style="margin-left: 7.75em;">I’d waken with the chickadees&mdash;their chorus&mdash;</span> <br />
<span class="line-indent" style="margin-left: 4em;">snip the strapping on an outsized bale of papers&mdash;   </p>
<p>get them loaded for my morning route. My father<br />
<span class="line-indent" style="margin-left: 7.75em;">never lay in late. Unshaven&mdash;with a picnic mug </p>
<p><span class="line-indent" style="margin-left: 4em;">of Folgers&mdash;he’d sit and thumb the funnies&mdash;pull</span><br />
his boots on in the entry when I ambled into view.</p>
<p><span class="line-indent" style="margin-left: 7.75em;">Together&mdash;in our solitudes&mdash;we’d throw the last</span><br />
<span class="line-indent" style="margin-left: 4em;">few bundles in the hatchback&mdash;cruise the boulevards</span></p>
<p>and crescents as if looking for a runaway&mdash;the old man<br />
<span class="line-indent" style="margin-left: 7.75em;">slowing down for me to bring the world the news.
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>The post <a href="https://thewalrus.ca/map-poem/">Map</a> first appeared on <a href="https://thewalrus.ca">The Walrus</a>.]]></content:encoded>

		
		
